modules.description: Handles event channel operations such as binding, unbinding, and signaling between domains. Works with event channel ports and interrupt descriptors to manage asynchronous notifications. Used to coordinate data transfer between guest domains and the hypervisor in MirageOS-based systems.

Provides functions to manage event channels and asynchronous operations, including retrieving event counts, file descriptors, and pending events. Works with event handles, file descriptors, and arrays of ports to coordinate event-driven workflows. Used to start and control event processing threads, handle event callbacks, and synchronize event-based execution.
